getCustomBlockIds

public short[] getCustomBlockIds()
Returns the array that is backing the block id data for this chunk. If the contents of the array are altered, setDirty(true) must be used so that the updated contents will be saved. Alternatively, use setCustomBlockIds(array) when you are finished manipulating the array and it will set the dirty flag for you.

Returns:
array of block id data for this chunk

setCustomBlockIds

public void setCustomBlockIds(short[] ids)
Sets the array that is used for the block id data for this chunk. This array will override any existing data, and wipe it out, so be sure this is what you intend to do.

Parameters:
ids - to set
